.TH DOTMATRIX 1 "March 2026" "dotmatrix 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dotmatrix \- project compositor with git versioning
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dotmatrix
[\fB\-\-json\fR]
.I command
[\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dotmatrix
is a project compositor that tracks files scattered across your system without moving them.
Each project gets its own isolated git repository for independent version history.
Files stay native to their tools on disk while dotmatrix tracks, versions, and backs them up.
.PP
Supports per-file encryption using the age standard for sensitive files.
.PP
Works on Linux, macOS, and Windows.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-json
Output results in JSON format for scripting and automation.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS init
Initialize dotmatrix configuration and data directories. Creates config file,
manifest, index, and sets up the data directory structure.
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix init
dotmatrix init --json
.fi
.RE
.SS new \fIname\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
Create a new project with optional description.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-description " " \fItext\fR
Project description.
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix new myproject
dotmatrix new myproject -d "My configuration files"
.fi
.RE
.SS delete \fIname\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
Delete a project from the manifest. Does not delete the actual tracked files.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Skip confirmation prompt.
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix delete myproject --force
.fi
.RE
.SS list [\fIoptions\fR]
List all projects.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Show detailed information including file counts and status.
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix list
dotmatrix list -v
dotmatrix list --json
.fi
.RE
.SS info \fIproject\fR
Show detailed information about a project including files, status, and git remote.
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix info myproject
dotmatrix info myproject --json
.fi
.RE
.SS add \fIproject\fR \fIfiles\fR... [\fIoptions\fR]
Add files to a project.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-track " " \fImode\fR
Track mode: git, backup, or both. Default: git.
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-encrypted
Mark files as encrypted (requires password for backup/restore).
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix add myproject ~/.bashrc ~/.zshrc
dotmatrix add myproject ~/.ssh/config -t backup -e
dotmatrix add myproject ~/Documents/notes.md -t both
.fi
.RE
.SS remove \fIproject\fR \fIfiles\fR...
Remove files from a project. Does not delete the actual files.
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix remove myproject ~/.bashrc
.fi
.RE
.SS status [\fIproject\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
Show status of tracked files. If no project specified, shows all projects.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-changes
Show only files that need attention (drifted, new, missing).
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix status
dotmatrix status myproject
dotmatrix status -c
dotmatrix status --json
.fi
.RE
.PP
Status symbols:
.RS
.TP
.B \[u2713]
Synced - file matches last known state
.TP
.B \[u26A0]
Drifted - file changed since last sync
.TP
.B +
New - file never synced
.TP
.B \[u2717]
Missing - file removed from disk
.RE
.SS sync [\fIproject\fR]
Mark drifted files as synced. Updates the index with current file state.
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix sync
dotmatrix sync myproject
.fi
.RE
.SS backup [\fIproject\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
Backup project files to content-addressed store with git versioning.
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-message " " \fItext\fR
Custom commit message for the backup.
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-archive
Create an archive backup (tar.gz/zip) instead of incremental.
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIformat\fR
Archive format: tar-gz, zip, seven-z. Default: tar-gz.
.TP
.BR \-\-password\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
Read encryption password from file. Required for encrypted files in non-interactive mode.
.TP
.BR \-\-password\-stdin
Read encryption password from stdin. Useful for piping from password managers.
.PP
The \fBDOTMATRIX_PASSWORD\fR environment variable can also be used as a fallback.
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix backup
dotmatrix backup myproject -m "Updated config"
dotmatrix backup myproject --archive --format zip
dotmatrix backup --password-file ~/.dotmatrix-pass
echo "mypass" | dotmatrix backup --password-stdin
.fi
.RE
.SS restore \fIproject\fR [\fIfiles\fR...] [\fIoptions\fR]
Restore files from the backup store.
.TP
.BR \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be restored without making changes.
.TP
.BR \-\-password\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
Read decryption password from file.
.TP
.BR \-\-password\-stdin
Read decryption password from stdin.
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix restore myproject
dotmatrix restore myproject ~/.bashrc
dotmatrix restore myproject --dry-run
dotmatrix restore myproject --password-file ~/.dotmatrix-pass
.fi
.RE
.SS git \fIproject\fR \fIaction\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
Git operations for a project's repository.
.PP
.B Actions:
.TP
.B remote [\-\-set \fIurl\fR]
Show or set the git remote URL.
.TP
.B push
Push commits to remote.
.TP
.B pull
Pull from remote.
.TP
.B fetch
Fetch from remote without merging.
.TP
.B log [\-c \fIcount\fR]
Show recent commits. Default: 10.
.TP
.B status
Show ahead/behind status relative to remote.
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix git myproject remote
dotmatrix git myproject remote --set git@github.com:user/repo.git
dotmatrix git myproject push
dotmatrix git myproject pull
dotmatrix git myproject log -c 5
dotmatrix git myproject status
.fi
.RE
.SS archives \fIproject\fR
List archive backups for a project.
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix archives myproject
dotmatrix archives myproject --json
.fi
.RE
.SS store [\fIproject\fR]
Show store statistics (size, file count). If no project specified, shows all.
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix store
dotmatrix store myproject
dotmatrix store --json
.fi
.RE
.SS tui
Launch the terminal user interface.
.SS gui
Launch the graphical user interface.
.SH TRACK MODES
.TP
.B git
Version controlled, diffable, shareable. Good for text files.
.TP
.B backup
Incremental content-addressed storage. Good for binary files.
.TP
.B both
Track via both git and backup.
.SH ENCRYPTION
Files can be marked as encrypted when adding to a project:
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix add myproject ~/.ssh/config -e
.fi
.RE
.PP
Encrypted files require a password for backup and restore operations.
Encryption uses the \fBage\fR standard (age-encryption.org).
.SS Password Methods (priority order)
.TP
.B 1. --password-stdin
Read from stdin. Good for scripts and password managers.
.RS
.nf
pass show dotmatrix | dotmatrix backup --password-stdin
.fi
.RE
.TP
.B 2. --password-file FILE
Read from a file. Good for cron jobs.
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix backup --password-file ~/.dotmatrix-pass
# Restrict permissions:
chmod 600 ~/.dotmatrix-pass
.fi
.RE
.TP
.B 3. DOTMATRIX_PASSWORD environment variable
Fallback option.
.RS
.nf
export DOTMATRIX_PASSWORD="mypassword"
dotmatrix backup
.fi
.RE
.TP
.B 4. Interactive prompt
If no password provided, prompts interactively.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic workflow
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Initialize dotmatrix
dotmatrix init

# Create a project
dotmatrix new shell-config -d "Shell configuration"

# Add files
dotmatrix add shell-config ~/.bashrc ~/.zshrc

# Check status
dotmatrix status shell-config

# Backup
dotmatrix backup shell-config -m "Initial backup"

# Set up git remote
dotmatrix git shell-config remote --set git@github.com:user/shell-config.git

# Push to remote
dotmatrix git shell-config push
.fi
.RE
.SS Encrypted files
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Add encrypted file
dotmatrix add secrets ~/.aws/credentials -t backup -e

# Backup with password
dotmatrix backup secrets --password-file ~/.dotmatrix-pass

# Restore
dotmatrix restore secrets --password-file ~/.dotmatrix-pass
.fi
.RE
.SS Archive backups
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Create tar.gz archive
dotmatrix backup myproject --archive

# Create zip archive
dotmatrix backup myproject --archive --format zip

# List archives
dotmatrix archives myproject
.fi
.RE
.SS Scripting with JSON output
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Get project list as JSON
dotmatrix list --json | jq '.projects[].name'

# Check if any files need backup
dotmatrix status --json | jq '.projects[].drifted'

# Automated backup script
if [ "$(dotmatrix status --json | jq '.projects[0].drifted')" -gt 0 ]; then
    dotmatrix backup
fi
.fi
.RE
.SS Cron job
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Create password file
echo "your-secure-password" > ~/.dotmatrix-pass
chmod 600 ~/.dotmatrix-pass

# Add to crontab (crontab -e)
0 2 * * * /usr/bin/dotmatrix backup --password-file ~/.dotmatrix-pass -m "Daily backup"
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.SS Linux
.TP
.I ~/.config/dotmatrix/config.toml
Configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/dotmatrix/manifest.toml
Project manifest defining tracked files.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/dotmatrix/projects/
Per-project data directories.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/dotmatrix/backups/
Archive backup storage.
.SS macOS
.TP
.I ~/Library/Application Support/dotmatrix/
Configuration and data directory.
.SS Windows
.TP
.I %APPDATA%\\dotmatrix\\
Configuration directory.
.TP
.I %LOCALAPPDATA%\\dotmatrix\\
Data directory.
.SS Per-Project Structure
.PP
Each project in \fI~/.local/share/dotmatrix/projects/<name>/\fR contains:
.TP
.I .git/
Project-specific git repository.
.TP
.I store/
Content-addressed file storage.
.TP
.I index.json
File tracking index with hashes and metadata.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred.
